[1] Pakistan - Khyber Pakhtunkhwa - media report & End Polio Pakistan
Date: Mon 8 Jul 2019, 3:38 PM
Source: Urdu Point [edited]
https://www.urdupoint.com/en/pakistan/four-more-polio-cases-found-in-pakistan-664170.html


Amid propaganda against the polio vaccine and refusal by parents to inoculate their children against the virus, 4 more polio cases have been diagnosed in Pakistan. Not a single of the victims had been vaccinated against the disease during immunization campaigns. According to a notification of the National Institute of Health (NIH), Islamabad, 2 of the 4 children with polio virus hailed from Khyber Pakhtunkhwa while others 2 from Balochistan.

Polio virus was confirmed in 2.5 years-old child from Union Council Haveed of District Bannu and another one year-old girl from UC Janikhel also reported to polio virus. Two kids from Jaffarabad and Qila Abdullah districts of Balochistan were also affected from polio virus.

With the latest addition, the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province, including the newly merged tribal districts, shares 25 of the total 41 cases reported across the country so far this year [2019], while 2 cases from Sindh, 3 from Punjab and 8 cases reported from Baluchistan. In a sharp contrast, last year [2018] 12 cases were reported from across the country and only 8 in 2017.

[Byline: Mohammad Ali]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The above media report is confirmed on the End Polio Pakistan website with the total number of cases of WPV1 confirmed with date of onset since 1 Jan 2019 in Pakistan now at 41. This is the highest number of annual cases reported since 2015 when there were 50 cases reported (http://www.endpolio.com.pk/polioin-pakistan/polio-cases-in-provinces. While the 2 cases reported from Balochistan are the 1st cases confirmed for this year, it is not surprising as there have been positive environmental samples reported during the course of the year (2019). See section [3] below for an example of the social impact the vaccination activities have had on the population.

For a map of Pakistan showing districts, see https://reliefweb.int/sites/reliefweb.int/files/resources/pak215_pakistan_districts_v5_a0_20181203.pdf; HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Pakistan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6559219,140.
- Mod.MPP]

