[The weekly report shows the continued circulation of WPV1 in Pakistan and Afghanistan as evidenced by the confirmation of new cases of AFP (acute flaccid paralysis) associated with infection with the WPV and continued positive environmental samples, fairly widespread circulation in Pakistan. A similar picture is seen with respect to cVDPV (circulating vaccine derived poliovirus) with new outbreaks being identified (DR Congo and Angola) and positive environmental samples).

There are 14 countries that have had documentation of poliovirus circulation in the past 12 months either through positive AFP cases or positive environmental samples. Enough said here.

